Job Title: 2X EL1 Lead Business Intelligence Analysts LH-05148
Ad Text:
Competitive Hourly Rates | Hybrid Working Arrangements | Working to Benefit at Risk Australians

Your new company

We are an independent agency that works within government rules and standards. Our goal is to make a positive difference in people's lives. We value people and put them first. We grow together by working as a team to achieve great results. We aim higher by staying strong and always looking for ways to improve. We take care by taking responsibility and doing the right thing. These values show our commitment to creating a positive and supportive culture.

Your new role


Provide high level technical and analytical expertise to initiatives of the Data and Analytics Branch.
Contribute to the design, build and implementation of reports, dashboards, analytic and data products that support business processes and deliver business insight.
Working with stakeholders to identify opportunities to leverage data and analytics to support consistent and efficient decision-making.
Influence business process and design to implement best practice information management and reporting principles.
Articulate complex information into simple messages that can be consumed by key stakeholders with varied levels of data literacy.
Contribute to best practice across the Data and Analytics Branch to ensure consistent analytics methodology and approach.
Mentor and lead junior analysts

What you'll need to succeed


Essential criteria

Significant experience in data analysis

Significant programming expertise (4+ years, SAS, SQL, R, Python)

Proven ability to deliver under limited supervision

Experience/strong familiarity with the use of data exploration and visualisation tools (e.g. PowerBI, Tableau, SAS Visual Analytics)

Experience working in an industrialised EDW environment.

Experience working within project management frameworks, the tools, and phases of the project lifecycle


Desirable criteria

Experience with SAS Enterprise Guide and/or Sas Viya

Experience mentoring junior analysts

Familiarity with Salesforce CRM and Analytics studio

Willingness to adapt to other analytics platforms and programming languages should the need arise


What you'll get in return


12-Month Contract

Hybrid Work Arrangements

Competitive Hourly Rates


What you need to do now

If you're interested in this role, click 'apply now' to forward an up-to-date copy of your CV, or call us now.

If this job isn't quite right for you, but you are looking for a new position, please contact us for a confidential discussion about your career.

FinXL by Randstad Digital focuses on accelerating client's digital and AI transformation journeys by providing specialised skills, managed programs, and strategic consulting across various industries.

Business Analyst background

Experience in confluence, JIRA and SharePoint
Experience in workshop facilitation

Job Title: Senior Manager Risk Culture and Capability
Ad Text:
Step into a high-impact role where your vision shapes enterprise-wide risk capability, drives cultural change, and positions you as a trusted advisor to executive leadership.

Why join us?

You'll get 14% super as standard, to help your future come alive.
Unleash your potential and build a career to be proud of through excellent training and development opportunities.
Balance your work between in-person days at our purpose-built hubs and working from home.
In the office, enjoy end of trip facilities, a yoga and multi-faith room, parent and carer rooms, quiet rooms, BrewHub coffee facilities, and collaborative team spaces.

About the role

As the Senior Manager, Risk Culture & Capability at Australian Retirement Trust, you’ll be at the forefront of shaping and embedding a high-performing risk culture across the organisation. Reporting to the General Manager, you’ll lead the design and delivery of innovative frameworks and programs that drive strong risk behaviours, clear accountability, and uplift capability at every level. This is a high-impact, strategic role where you’ll partner with senior leaders, influence mindsets, and ensure ART not only meets but exceeds regulatory expectations. If you’re passionate about culture transformation and thrive in a dynamic, values-driven environment, this is your opportunity to make a lasting difference.




Key aspects of the role include:

Lead the development and implementation of ART’s enterprise-wide Risk Culture Strategy and Framework.
Design and deliver targeted risk capability uplift programs for leaders and staff.
Champion a values-aligned, transparent risk culture in partnership with executive and frontline leaders.
Conduct risk culture assessments using qualitative and quantitative methods.
Define and report on key risk culture metrics to senior leadership and Board committees.
Collaborate with People & Impact to embed risk capability into talent and leadership programs.
Act as a trusted advisor to the Chief Risk Officer and executive team on culture, governance, and accountability.
Ensure all initiatives align with APRA standards and regulatory expectations.
Build and lead a high-performing team of Risk Culture Specialists.
Drive continuous improvement through data-driven insights and stakeholder feedback.

This role is a permanent opportunity based in Brisbane, Sydney, or Melbourne

About you

It goes without saying you'll be a great communicator with top notch interpersonal skills. We'll also expect you to pick up problems and come up with quick, creative ways to solve them. It's quite likely you tick some of the following boxes too:  

Proven experience designing and delivering culture, leadership, or capability uplift initiatives in complex organisations.
Strong expertise in developing and using culture measurement tools, surveys, and behavioural diagnostics.
Demonstrated ability to lead and develop high-performing teams, fostering collaboration and professional growth.
Exceptional stakeholder engagement and influencing skills, with a track record of partnering with executive leaders and cross-functional teams.
Deep understanding of risk management principles, APRA prudential standards (especially SPS 220 and SPS 510), and regulatory expectations.
Advanced analytical skills with the ability to interpret complex data, identify trends, and provide actionable insights.
Outstanding written and verbal communication skills, including experience presenting to Boards and senior executives.
Strategic thinker with the ability to translate vision into practical, enterprise-wide implementation plans.
Experience collaborating with HR, L&D, and business leaders on people and culture strategies.
Relevant tertiary and/or post-graduate qualifications in risk management, organisational psychology, business, or a related field (highly regarded).

About us

Our 2.4 million members trust us to take care of over $330 billion in retirement savings. And we help them take charge of their finances and face the future with confidence. Our inclusive culture means you’ll be valued and heard in a respectful workplace. We've created an environment where you can be yourself and do amazing work. It's that simple.

Apply online now

Everyone is welcome to apply. We value diverse thinking, cultures, perspectives, backgrounds, and abilities. Awaken your career at Australian Retirement Trust and apply now. Applications close 7th December 2025.

We don’t want to leave you with a monstrous wait. So, you’ll hear from us after the closing date to find out whether you’ve made it through to the next round or not. Being fair and up-front is important to us – and recruitment is no different.

Job Title: Senior Manager Risk Governance, Systems & Insights
Ad Text:
Championing strategic clarity and innovation, you’ll shape the future of risk management by integrating cutting-edge technology, fostering collaboration, and delivering actionable insights that keep Australian Retirement Trust ahead of industry standards and regulatory expectations.

Why join us?

You'll get 14% super as standard, to help your future come alive.
Unleash your potential and build a career to be proud of through excellent training and development opportunities.
Balance your work between in-person days at our purpose-built hubs and working from home.
In the office, enjoy end of trip facilities, a yoga and multi-faith room, parent and carer rooms, quiet rooms, BrewHub coffee facilities, and collaborative team spaces.

About the role

As Senior Manager, Risk Governance, Systems & Insights, you will play a pivotal leadership role in shaping the risk management landscape at Australian Retirement Trust. You’ll be responsible for designing, implementing, and continuously enhancing risk frameworks, systems, and enterprise reporting that support informed decision-making at the highest levels. This role requires deep expertise in governance, policy management, and risk technology, with a focus on delivering timely, high-quality insights to the Executive and Board. You’ll collaborate across all areas of the organisation to ensure governance clarity, policy consistency, and regulatory compliance under APRA’s prudential standards. If you’re passionate about driving strategic risk initiatives and uplifting governance maturity, this is your opportunity to make a significant impact.




Key aspects of the role include:

Lead the design, implementation, and ongoing enhancement of ART’s risk frameworks and governance structures.
Oversee enterprise risk reporting, delivering actionable insights to the Executive and Board Risk Committee.
Manage the risk management policy suite, ensuring alignment with regulatory and strategic changes.
Own the strategic direction and operational management of risk systems and technology platforms.
Coordinate system maintenance, upgrades, and enhancements for robust, user-friendly risk technology.
Standardise risk reporting templates and uplift reporting quality across risk domains.
Support regulatory reviews, internal audits, and policy development to meet APRA standards.
Foster collaboration across the organisation to enhance risk accountability and governance practices.
Build and lead a high-performing team of risk professionals, driving capability development and continuous improvement.
Monitor regulatory developments and act as a liaison for governance-related queries from regulators, auditors, and assurance providers.

This role is a permanent opportunity based in Brisbane, Sydney, or Melbourne

Coordinate system maintenance, upgrades, and enhancements for robust, user-friendly risk technology.
Standardise risk reporting templates and uplift reporting quality across risk domains.
Support regulatory reviews, internal audits, and policy development to meet APRA standards.
Foster collaboration across the organisation to enhance risk accountability and governance practices.
Build and lead a high-performing team of risk professionals, driving capability development and continuous improvement.
Monitor regulatory developments and act as a liaison for governance-related queries from regulators, auditors, and assurance providers.

Our Data Engineering Team is comprised of data experts. We build world-class data solutions and applications that power crucial business decisions throughout the organisation. We manage multiple analytical data models and pipelines across Atlassian, covering finance, growth, product analysis, customer analysis, sales and marketing, and so on. We maintain Atlassian's data lake that provide a unified way of analysing our customers, our products, our operations, and the interactions among them.

We're hiring a Senior Data Engineer, reporting to the Data Engineering Manager based in Sydney. Here, you'll enable a world-class engineering practice, drive the approach with which we use data, develop backend systems and data models to serve the needs of insights, and help build Atlassian's data-driven culture. You love thinking about the ways the business can consume data and then figuring out how to build it

Working at Atlassian

Atlassians can choose where they work – whether in an office, from home, or a combination of the two. That way, Atlassians have more control over supporting their family, personal goals, and other priorities. We can hire people in any country where we have a legal entity.

You'll partner with the product analytics and data scientist team to build the data solutions that allow them to obtain more insights from our data and use that to support important business decisions.

You'll work with different stakeholders to understand their needs and architect/build the data models, data acquisition/ingestion processes and data applications to address those requirements.

You'll add new sources, code business rules, and produce new metrics that support the product analysts and data scientists.

You'll be the data domain expert who understand all the nitty-gritty of our products.

You'll own a problem end-to-end. Requirements could be vague, and iterations will be rapid

You'll improve data quality by using & improving internal tools/frameworks to automatically detect DQ issues.

A BS in Computer Science or equivalent experience with 5+ years of professional experience as a Sr. Data Engineer or in a similar role.

Strong programming skills using Python

Working knowledge of relational databases and query authoring (SQL).

Experience designing data models for optimal storage and retrieval to meet product and business requirements.

Experience building scalable data pipelines using Spark (SparkSQL) with Airflow scheduler/executor framework or similar scheduling tools.

Experience working with AWS data services or similar Apache projects (Spark, Flink, Hive, and Kafka).

Understanding of Data Engineering tools/frameworks and standards to improve the productivity and quality of output for Data Engineers across the team.

Well versed in modern software development practices (Agile, TDD, CICD)

Benefits & Perks

Atlassian offers a wide range of perks and benefits designed to support you, your family and to help you engage with your local community. Our offerings include health and wellbeing resources, paid volunteer days, and so much more. To learn more, visit go.atlassian.com/perksandbenefits.

About Atlassian

At Atlassian, we're motivated by a common goal: to unleash the potential of every team. Our software products help teams all over the planet and our solutions are designed for all types of work. Team collaboration through our tools makes what may be impossible alone, possible together.

We believe that the unique contributions of all Atlassians create our success. To ensure that our products and culture continue to incorporate everyone's perspectives and experience, we never discriminate based on race, religion, national origin, gender identity or expression, sexual orientation, age, or marital, veteran, or disability status. All your information will be kept confidential according to EEO guidelines.

To provide you the best experience, we can support with accommodations or adjustments at any stage of the recruitment process. Simply inform our Recruitment team during your conversation with them.

To learn more about our culture and hiring process, visit go.atlassian.com/crh.
